transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling Viagra. This is Jimmy. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Yeah, Jimmy. I called last month to cancel this order and lo and behold I got another one in the mail today.

Speaker 1: All right, let me try to pull your information up and see what I see. Can I get your phone number, please?

Speaker 2: 234.

Speaker 1: 600 6865?

Speaker 2: Okay, maybe I got it wrong. Did you say 834-600?

Speaker 1: 234.

Speaker 2: Okay, 234. Okay, repeat it to me again so I'll make sure I have it correct.

Speaker 1: 234.

Speaker 2: 234-600.

Speaker 1: Mm-hmm.

Speaker 2: 6865.

Speaker 1: 6865. Okay, great.

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: All right, this is Bruce I'm speaking to.

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: All right, Bruce. I'm having a count up. I do see that you're currently getting the Viagra 50 milligrams. It looks like that you're getting 25 of them every two months.

Speaker 1: I don't see any other notes on the account that you tried to cancel in the past, but I can go and help you out.

Speaker 1: Any particular reason why you want to cancel? You don't mind me asking?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I don't need them anymore, my friend.

Speaker 1: Okay. How are they working out for you? Just curious. 50 milligrams. How are those doing?

Speaker 2: I ended up getting these knockout pills and they're ridiculous. You take one a day and they're ridiculous.

Speaker 1: Okay. So I guess that means they're working out for you, but just be careful when you take these things. Make sure they're FDA approved.

Speaker 2: Yes, they are.

Speaker 1: Okay. And they're called knockout pills?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: All right. So Bruce, I can go ahead and take care of your request for you, but I do have to tell you, since you were on a prescription with us, if you do decide to cancel,

Speaker 2: it'll be difficult to try to order in the future because we're on a first come, first serve basis, because we're also the only Viagra that's FDA approved,

Speaker 1: coming from the Pfizer labs in France, because that's our trademark. And it's the real Viagra, basically.

Speaker 2: But if you do cancel the prescription, that means it'll be difficult to try to order in the future, as I mentioned again, because we're always usually sold out. Okay?

Speaker 1: That's okay.

Speaker 2: All right. So I'll go ahead and take care of your request for you. I hate to lose you. You're a customer that was a VIP with us, and if it's coming too often, we can push that back so it's not coming so often.

Speaker 1: No, the last one I had, I never even took any out. I still have the whole bottle I had the last time.

Speaker 2: All right. Not a problem. So I went ahead and took care of that for you. Is there anything else I can do for you today?

Speaker 1: That's all. Thank you.

Speaker 2: No problem. You have a great day.

Speaker 1: You too. Bye-bye.
